(b) Regression line

# simulate the weight 
# assuming weight has mean 120 pounds, sd of 15 pounds
log_height <- rnorm(1000, mean=log(6), sd=log(1.1))
# assuming a relationship between height and weight
error <- rnorm(1000, mean=0, sd=0.25)
log_weight <- -3.5 + 2.0 * log_height + error
# plot weight and height
plot(log_height,log_weight)

fit4a <- lm(log_weight ~ log_height)
summary(fit4a)

(c) Intepretation

After log-transformation of both nitrix acid and mortality, coefficient means how much percent mortality will increase when the nitric acid increase 1%, here its exp(0.0159), which should be very close to 0.0159%. If just log-transform the mortality, coefficient means how many percents mortality will increase when increase nitric acid by 1 unit.
